==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Restorative
<hw>Re*stor"a*tive</hw> <pr>(r?*st?r"?*t?v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>restoratif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to
restoration; having power to restore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Destroys life's enemy,⟦br⟧
Hunger, with sweet <qex>restorative</qex> delight.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Restorative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Restorative
<hw>Re*stor"a*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Something which serves to
restore; especially, a restorative medicine.</def>
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Restoratively</ent>⟦br⟧
